➜英语的快乐，就在于每次不断的学习和记忆
http://www.sohu.com/a/391340198_661620	22010
<p>In the end the skills of the bottom half of the population affect the wages of the top half. If the bottom half can not effectively staff the processes that have to be operated, the management that go with these processes will disappear.</p>
<p><strong>（一）考点词汇</strong></p>
<p>1. in the end 最后</p>
<p>例句：They prefer, in the end, to stick with what they know. </p>
<p>他们最终选择了继续做自己熟悉的事。</p>
<p>2. the bottom half 后一半</p>
<p>例句：He's in the bottom half of the class. </p>
<p>他在班上的名次位于后一半.</p>
<p>3. affect 影响(verb)</p>
<p>例句：Poor housing and family stress can affect both physical and mental health. </p>
<p>住房条件差、家庭压力大会影响身心两方面的健康。</p>
<p><strong>注：一组易混淆的词</strong></p>
<p>affect通常为动词：影响</p>
<p>effect通常为名词：影响，效果</p>
<p>例句：effect of music on their behavior...</p>
<p>音乐对他们行为的影响</p>
<p>infect为动词，感染</p>
<p>例句：A mosquito can infect a large number of people. </p>
<p>一只蚊子就可以感染很多人。</p>
<p>4. the top half 上半部</p>
<p>例句：America does not rank in the top half of all advanced nations when it comes to math. </p>
<p>在数学方面，美国没有进入发达国家排名的上半区。</p>
<p>5. staff </p>
<p>作名词，意思为“全体工作人员”。</p>
<p>例句：The outpatient program has a staff of six people.</p>
<p>门诊部有 6 名工作人员。</p>
<p>作动词，意思为“在…工作，任职于”</p>
<p>例句：The center is staffed with highly trained physicians.</p>
<p>该中心配备了训练有素的医生。</p>
<p>6. operate 操作</p>
<p>例句：A massive rock fall trapped the men as they operated a tunnelling machine.</p>
<p>这些工人在操作隧道挖掘机时被大量的落石困住了。</p>
<p>7. disappear 消失</p>
<p>例句：The black car drove away from them and disappeared.</p>
<p>那辆黑色轿车驶离了他们的视线。</p>
<p><strong>（二）翻译</strong></p>
<p>In the end the skills of the bottom half of the population affect the wages of the top half. If the bottom half can not effectively staff the processes that have to be operated, the management that go with these processes will disappear.</p>
<p>最后，能力处于下半区的员工的技能水平会影响上半区人员的收入。如果下半区员工不能有效地供职于那些必须操作的流程，那么与这些流程配套的管理也就消失了。</p>
<p><strong>（三）复试口语</strong></p>
<p>1. I do believe that with solid educational background and rich working experience, I would be an excellent student of your MBA program.</p>
<p>我相信，有着扎实的教育背景和丰富的工作经验，我将是你们MBA课程的优秀学生。</p>
<p>2.I am always ready to be helpful and caring.</p>
<p>我乐于助人、关心他人。</p>
<p>3. I am very shy, but if you know me better, you will find out that I am very humorous and willing to make more friends.</p>
<p>虽然我很内向，但是如果你了解我，你会发现我很幽默也愿意与人交朋友。</p>
<p>注：humorous 幽默的</p>
<p><strong>（四）一勺鸡汤</strong></p>
<p>A man is not old as long as he is seeking something. A man is not old until regrets take the place of dreams.</p>
<p>只要一个人还有追求，他就没有老。什么时候后悔取代了梦想，一个人才算老。</p>
